oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Gasim, Seif
Abel, Stefan
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Cereals, pulses and oilseeds

oai_dc:dc.dc:description:
Conclusions:
Out-crossing rates of the population of winter beans is relatively high compared to the summer beans at Göttingen (58% in 1989, and 50,3 in 1990; Link et al. 1994)
